</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-story --></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-top-story --></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .round-up -->
<div class="round-up">
<div class="ru-top-story">
<h6 class="kicker"><a href="//dealbook.blogs.nytimes.com/category/ipoofferings/">I.P.O./OFFERINGS &#187;</a></h6>
<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">Chinese Auction House Raises $331 Million in Hong Kong I.P.O. <span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span></span><!-- end .title --> The offering by Poly Culture bolsters the prospects of the companyâs auction business in the worldâs fastest-growing art market and allows it to expand its cinema, theater and performance hall operations.<br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/02/28/poly-culture-a-chinese-auction-house-raises-331-million-in-hong-kong-i-p-o/">DealBook &#187;</a></span></p>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-story -->
<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">HubSpot Preparing for I.P.O. <span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span></span><!-- end .title --> HubSpot, an online marketing software company, is working with Morgan Stanley on a potential deal for its initial public offering, The Wall Street Journal writes, citing unidentified people familiar with the situation. The company is expected to go public this year.<br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//on.wsj.com/1cdCMzT">WALL STREET JOURNAL </a></span></p>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-story -->
<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">Saudi Arabia to List Biggest Bank <span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span></span><!-- end .title --> Saudi Arabiaâs finance minister announced that the country planned to float a 15 percent stake in National Commercial Bank, Saudi Arabiaâs biggest bank by assets, The Financial Times writes. Much of the initial public offering is expected to be reserved for locals at a marked-down price, as is customary in the Gulf.<br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//on.ft.com/1cW7jQL"> FINANCIAL TIMES </a></span></p>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-story -->
<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><img width="75" height="75" border="0" alt="SoftBankâs Investment in Alibaba May Turn Into a Burden" src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/02/28/business/dbpix-softbank/dbpix-softbank-square320.jpg"/><span class="title">SoftBankâs Investment in Alibaba May Turn Into a Burden <span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span></span><!-- end .title --> For now, SoftBank, through its stake in Alibaba, is one of the few ways for public investors to gain exposure to the Chinese e-commerce giant. But that advantage will disappear when Alibaba goes public, writes Una Galani of Reuters Breakingviews.<br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/02/27/softbanks-investment-in-alibaba-may-turn-into-a-burden/">DealBook &#187;</a></span></p>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-story --></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-top-story --></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .round-up -->
<div class="round-up">
<div class="ru-top-story">
<h6 class="kicker"><a href="//dealbook.blogs.nytimes.com/category/venture-capital/">VENTURE CAPITAL &#187;</a></h6>
<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">Start-Up That Analyzes Twitter for Wall Street Raises Financing <span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span></span><!-- end .title --> Eagle Alpha has raised $1.5 million in financing to expand in a growing field of sifting through social media and the web to glean information on stocks.<br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/02/27/start-up-that-analyzes-twitter-for-wall-street-raises-financing/">DealBook &#187;</a></span></p>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-story -->
<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">Institutional Venture Partners Opens San Francisco Office <span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span></span><!-- end .title --> Institutional Venture Partners is opening a new office in San Francisco, a move that reflects increasing venture capital investment there compared with Silicon Valley, The Wall Street Journal writes.<br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//blogs.wsj.com/venturecapital/2014/02/27/as-bay-area-investment-shifts-north-institutional-venture-partners-opens-san-francisco-office/"> WALL STREET JOURNAL </a></span></p>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-story --></div>
